-of-court-settlement-123090100324_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbyju-s-and-lenders-postpone-legal-battle-aim-for-out-of-court-settlement-123090100324_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20Habib%20Tanvir%20on%20His%20100th%20Birth%20Anniversary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01121010%2FUntitled-design-12.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20what%20I%20had%20to%20say%2C%20in%20aesthetics%2C%20in%20the%20performing%20arts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20what%20I%20had%20to%20say%20socially%2C%20politically%20%E2%80%93%20the%20medium%20was%20not%20the%20cinema%2C%20it%20was%20the%20theatre.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20Habib%20Tanvir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBorn%20on%20September%201%2C%201923%2C%20Habib%20Tanvir%20would%20have%20been%20100%20years%20old%20today.%20He%20was%2086%20when%20he%20died%20in%202009.%20His%20association%20with%20the%20stage%20remained%20intact%20until%20his%20death%2C%20spanning%20nearly%20three-quarters%20of%20his%20life.%20In%20the%20course%20of%20his%20long%20innings%20in%20theatre%2C%20the%20playwright-director%20did%20not%20only%20evolve%20a%20new%20style%20and%20idiom%20for%20his%20own%20work%3B%20he%20also%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20redefined%20the%20very%20concept%20of%20modernity%2C%20particularly%20in%20relation%20to%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20Tanvir%20had%20seen%20and%20participated%20in%20stage%20plays%20during%20his%20school%20days%20in%20Raipur%2C%20it%20was%20in%20the%201940s%20in%20Bombay%20that%20he%20came%20to%20be%20seriously%20involved%20in%20theatre%20when%20he%20joined%20the%20local%20chapter%20of%20the%20Indian%20People%E2%80%99s%20Theatre%20Association%20(IPTA).%20His%20journey%20in%20theatre%20brought%20forth%20a%20large%20and%20richly%20varied%20corpus%20of%20plays%2C%20which%20includes%20original%20texts%20as%20well%20as%20adaptations%20of%20Sanskrit%20and%20Elizabethan%20classics%2C%20Moliere%2C%20Zweig%2C%20Brecht%2C%20and%20Tagore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115109%2Fpic-2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22878%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115109%2Fpic-2.png%20750w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115109%2Fpic-2-300x96.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670992%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHabib%20Tanvir%20as%20the%20Rajpurohit%20in%20his%20signature%20play%2C%20Charandas%20Chor%2C%20Modinagar%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20October%202002.%20Photo%3A%20Sudhanva%20Deshpande%2FIndian%20Cultural%20Forum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20Tanvir%20got%20to%20Bombay%20is%20an%20interesting%20story%20in%20itself.%20He%20was%20in%20his%20early%2020s%2C%20pursuing%20his%20studies%20at%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20for%20a%20Master%E2%80%99s%20degree.%20Half%20way%20through%20it%20he%20decided%20to%20change%20course%20and%2C%20instead%2C%20explore%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20career%20in%20cinema.%20This%20required%20him%20to%20travel%20to%20Bombay.%20Since%20he%20did%20not%20have%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20train%20ticket%2C%20he%20applied%20for%20recruitment%20in%20the%20Royal%20Indian%20Navy%20which%20offered%20a%20return%20fare%20to%20enable%20applicants%20to%20travel%20to%20Bombay%20for%20preliminary%20interviews!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EObviously%2C%20Tanvir%20didn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20to%20the%20navy.%20Nor%20did%20he%20want%20to.%20But%20he%20was%20in%20Bombay%20now%20and%20that%20was%20what%20he%20had%20actually%20desired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20the%20whirl%20of%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20left-wing%20politics%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20were%20politically%20surcharged%20days.%20The%20environment%20was%20throbbing%20with%20revolutionary%20activism%20and%20Bombay%20was%20one%20of%20its%20major%20centres.%20In%20due%20course%2C%20the%20young%20Tanvir%20was%20also%20drawn%20to%20leftwing%20politics%20and%20became%20actively%20involved%20in%20its%20cultural%20movement%20which%20was%20led%20by%20the%20Progressive%20Writers%E2%80%99%20Association%20(PWA)%20and%20IPTA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20association%20with%20these%20organisations%20brought%20him%20in%20contact%20with%20stalwarts%20like%20Ali%20Sardar%20Jafri%2C%20Sajjad%20Zahir%2C%20and%20Shaukat%20and%20Kaifi%20Azmi%20as%20well%20as%20Balraj%20Sahni%2C%20Dina%20Pathak%2C%20Khwaja%20Ahmad%20Abbas%2C%20and%20Zohra%20Sehgal.%20These%20relationships%20helped%20him%20grow%20artistically%20and%20politically.%20It%20would%20not%20be%20wrong%20to%20say%20that%20Bombay%20was%20the%20crucible%20in%20which%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20social%20and%20cultural%20consciousness%20was%20tempered.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Ffrom-pyarey-mama-to-habib-tanvir-a-personal-tribute%5C%22%3EFrom%20%E2%80%98Pyarey%20Mama%E2%80%99%20to%20Habib%20Tanvir%3A%20A%20Personal%20Tribute%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETanvir%20used%20to%20tell%20of%20an%20interesting%20incident%20relating%20to%20his%20work%20with%20IPTA.%20Once%2C%20Balraj%20Sahni%20was%20directing%20a%20play%20in%20which%20Tanvir%20had%20a%20role%20and%20was%20required%20to%20shed%20tears%20in%20one%20scene.%20Balraj%20Sahni%20put%20him%20through%20the%20scene%20repeatedly%20but%20could%20not%20get%20him%20to%20perform%20the%20act%20convincingly.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20Balraj%20Sahni%20slapped%20him%20so%20hard%20on%20the%20face%20that%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20filled%20with%20tears.%20Sahni%20looked%20at%20him%20and%2C%20smiling%2C%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CGood.%20This%20is%20what%20is%20called%20muscle%20memory.%20Now%20you%20will%20never%20forget%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20left%20movement%20weakened%20and%20IPTA%20virtually%20became%20dysfunctional%2C%20Tanvir%20left%20Bombay%20and%20moved%20to%20Delhi%20in%201954.%20The%20reason%20that%20he%20cited%20for%20this%20move%20is%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20way%20of%20the%20temptation%20to%20act%20in%20films%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecause%20by%20then%20I%20had%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20in%20the%20cinema%20of%20those%20days%20there%20was%20no%20autonomy%20for%20the%20artist%20%E2%80%93%20you%20could%20not%20act%20the%20way%20you%20wanted%2C%20nor%20direct%20the%20way%20you%20wanted.%20The%20producer%2C%20who%20had%20no%20artistic%20sense%2C%20who%20was%20only%20a%20money%20bag%2C%20a%20financier%2C%20would%20meddle%20in%20the%20work%20of%20the%20director%2C%20actor%2C%20writer%2C%20everyone%E2%80%A6%20Anyhow%2C%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20I%20was%20convinced%20that%20I%20had%20something%20to%20say.%20And%20for%20what%20I%20had%20to%20say%2C%20in%20aesthetics%2C%20in%20the%20performing%20arts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20what%20I%20had%20to%20say%20socially%2C%20politically%20%E2%80%93%20the%20medium%20was%20not%20the%20cinema%2C%20it%20was%20the%20theatre.%20This%20was%20a%20very%20clear%20realisation%20in%20the%20early%20fifties%20which%20brought%20me%20to%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20new%20%E2%80%98stage%E2%80%99%20of%20life%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20Tanvir%20began%20with%20school%20children%2C%20writing%20and%20staging%20plays%20for%20and%20with%20them%2C%20before%20producing%20the%20first%20embryonic%20version%20of%20his%20celebrated%20play%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAgra%20Bazar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20First%20staged%20in%20the%20Okhla%20campus%20of%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%2C%20with%20teachers%2C%20students%20and%20residents%20of%20Okhla%20village%20in%20the%20cast%2C%20the%20play%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Nazir%20Day%20events%20organised%20by%20the%20Jamia%20chapter%20of%20PWA.%20It%20dramatised%20the%20work%2C%20life%20and%20times%20of%20an%20unusual%2018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%20Urdu%20poet%2C%20Nazir%20Akbarabadi.%20The%20production%2C%20although%20still%20in%20an%20early%20stage%2C%20not%20only%20marked%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20permanent%20relocation%20to%20Delhi%20but%20also%20his%20debut%20as%20a%20playwright-director%20on%20the%20theatre%20scene.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20in%201955%2C%20he%20went%20to%20England%20for%20theatre%20training%20and%20travelled%20extensively%20through%20Europe%2C%20watching%20plays%20and%20meeting%20directors%20and%20actors.%20He%20even%20travelled%20to%20Berlin%20with%20the%20express%20purpose%20of%20meeting%20the%20great%20German%20director%2C%20Bertolt%20Brecht.%20Although%20the%20meeting%20failed%20to%20materialise%20%E2%80%93%20Brecht%20died%20in%20Berlin%20in%20August%201956%20%E2%80%93%20Tanvir%20spent%20nearly%20eight%20months%20watching%20the%20performances%20at%20the%20Berliner%20Ensemble%2C%20sitting%20in%20on%20their%20rehearsals%2C%20and%20discussing%20the%20productions%20and%20Brecht%E2%80%99s%20theatre%20practice%20with%20artists%20like%20Helene%20Weigel%20and%20Elizabeth%20Hauptmann.%20He%20saw%20the%20practical%20examples%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBrecht%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cepic%E2%80%9D%20theory%20which%20offered%20a%20radical%20alternative%20to%20the%20artistic%20and%20social%20restrictions%20of%20the%20dominant%20individualist%20forms%20of%20middle-class%20drama.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQuest%20for%20a%20new%20theatrical%20idiom%3A%20the%20birth%20of%20Naya%20Theatre%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETanvir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20spent%20several%20years%20researching%20and%20studying%20folk%20traditions%20in%20drama%2C%20story-telling%2C%20music%2C%20and%20dance.%20He%20frequently%20wandered%20through%20the%20interiors%20of%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20living%20with%20and%20talking%20to%20local%20groups%20and%20individual%20performers%20.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20several%20long%20years%20of%20sustained%2C%20single-minded%20pursuit%20through%20exploration%20and%20experimentation%2C%20he%20eventually%20arrived%20at%20a%20theatre%20where%20he%20worked%20almost%20exclusively%20with%20village%20actors%20who%20brought%20with%20them%20their%20traditional%20style%20of%20acting.%20His%20productions%20not%20only%20used%20traditional%20performers%20but%20also%20made%20abundant%20use%20of%20folk%20music%20and%20musicians%20and%2C%20frequently%2C%20of%20folkloric%20narrative%20material.%20The%20language%20of%20his%20plays%2C%20too%2C%20became%20in%20large%20part%20the%20folk%20speech.%20In%20short%2C%20his%20plays%20were%20created%20in%20remarkably%20close%20proximity%20to%20the%20traditions%20of%20folk%20performance%20in%20India%20in%20general%20and%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20in%20particular.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETanvir%20always%20emphasised%20that%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20that%20he%20learnt%20from%20his%20European%20experience%20was%20that%20meaningful%20theatre%20was%20possible%20only%20if%20one%20built%20close%20to%20the%20traditions%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20people.%20This%20was%20also%20the%20lesson%20he%20had%20learnt%20from%20his%20IPTA%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20on%20returning%20to%20India%2C%20he%20began%20to%20actively%20explore%20the%20possibility%20of%20creating%20such%20a%20theatre.%20He%20began%20by%20including%20six%20village%20artists%20from%20Chhattisgarh%20in%20his%20first%20production%20after%20returning%20from%20Europe%3A%20Sudraka%E2%80%99s%20Sanskrit%20classic%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMritchchakatikam%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Etranslated%20into%20Hindustani%20as%20%E2%80%98Mitti%20ki%20Gaadi%E2%80%99).%20This%20was%20his%20first%20and%20limited%20engagement%20with%20the%20folk%20performers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115544%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115544%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115544%2FUntitled-design-10-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01115544%2FUntitled-design-10-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670993%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHabib%20Tanvir%20first%20engaged%20with%20folk%20performers%20in%20his%20production%20of%20Sudraka%E2%80%99s%20Sanskrit%20classic%2C%20Mritchchakatikam%20(translated%20into%20Hindustani%20as%3Cbr%3E%E2%80%98Mitti%20ki%20Gaadi%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20years%20later%2C%20it%20developed%20into%20a%20full-fledged%20partnership%20between%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20educated%2C%20formally%20trained%20consciousness%20and%20the%20natural%20talent%20and%20skills%20of%20his%20village%20artists.%20This%20partnership%20was%20what%20defined%20his%20repertory%20company%2C%20Naya%20Theatre%2C%20and%20set%20it%20apart%20from%20all%20other%20drama%20groups%20of%20the%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI