20make%20up%20Omair%20Ahmad%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ETall%20Tales%20by%20a%20Small%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20single%20rapt%20sitting.%20By%20the%20time%20a%20reader%20has%20done%20so%2C%C2%A0it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20author%20has%20made%20his%20inheritance%20his%20own.%20Set%20in%20Gorakhpur%2C%20these%20stories%20are%20so%20comfortably%20Gorakhpuri%2C%20they%20are%20their%20own%20affirmation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%2C%20let%20me%20state%20that%20Omair%20is%20a%20friend%2C%20but%20well%20before%20I%20knew%20him%2C%20I%20read%20his%20novella%20%3Cem%3EStoryTeller%E2%80%99s%20Tale%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20book%20achieved%20something%20rather%20unique%20%E2%80%93%20transcreating%20a%20storyteller%E2%80%99s%20oral%20world%20into%20words%2C%20drawing%20from%20and%20capturing%20the%20cadence%20of%20Hindustani%20in%20English%20prose.%20As%20a%20TV%20journalist%20I%20know%20what%20a%20stunning%20feat%20this%20is%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20world%20as%20it%20is%20cannot%20just%20be%20recorded%20on%20camera%20and%20transcribed%20for%20it%20to%20become%20real%20on%20the%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20273px)%2085vw%2C%20273px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31162010%2F71fswkzjJRL.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22273%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31162010%2F71fswkzjJRL.jpeg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31162010%2F71fswkzjJRL-196x300.jpeg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31162010%2F71fswkzjJRL-667x1024.jpeg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670876%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22419%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOmair%20Ahmad%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ETall%20Tales%20By%20a%20Small%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ESpeaking%20Tiger%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20distinctive%20ability%20runs%20through%20his%20fiction%2C%20though%20each%20book%20is%20strikingly%20different.%20It%20is%20very%20much%20in%20evidence%20in%20%3Cem%3ETall%20Tales%20by%20a%20Small%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20an%20invitation%2C%20like%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekissagoi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20to%20hear%20some%20tall%20tales.%20The%20writing%20is%20sharp%2C%20from%20the%20plot%20twists%20to%20the%20humour%20and%20irony%20%E2%80%93%20and%20speaks%20directly%20to%20many%20of%20us%20today%20who%20read%20largely%20in%20English%20but%20still%20inhabit%20an%20emotional%20world%20shaped%20by%20the%20mother-tongues%20of%20our%20parents%20or%20grandparents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGorakhpur%20is%20the%20muse%2C%20and%20Kallu%20Maharaj%2C%20the%20narrator%20is%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Ca%20small%20dog%20of%20indeterminate%20colour%20and%20parentage%2C%20with%20a%20tendency%20to%20tuck%20in%20his%20tail%20and%20skitter%20away%20at%20the%20slightest%20sense%20of%20danger%E2%80%A6only%20to%20return%2C%20courting%20danger%20from%20a%20distance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0As%20we%20settle%20down%20to%20our%20image%20of%20the%20narrator%2C%20Omair%2C%20the%20writer%2C%20speaks%20directly%20to%20us%2C%20shaking%20out%20complacent%20acceptance%20of%20this%20description%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWars%20have%20been%20won%20in%20such%20fashion%2C%20so%20for%20this%2C%20I%20will%20not%20judge%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmair%20told%20me%20he%20had%20considered%20telling%20these%20tales%20through%20three%20characters%20%E2%80%93%20an%20SHO%2C%20a%20village%20%3Cem%3Emukhia%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20a%20dog%20%E2%80%93%20before%20he%20settled%20on%20Kallu%20Maharaj%2C%20because%20who%20else%20would%20know%20the%20streets%20of%20our%20towns%20and%20cities%20better%20than%20a%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outside%20world%20in%20such%20towns%20is%20a%20masculine%20world%2C%20and%20that%20is%20the%20world%20we%20see%20reflected%20in%20these%20stories.%20The%20first%20of%20the%20stories%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Dog%20Thrower%20of%20Chote%20Qazipur%E2%80%99%2C%20establishes%20the%20world%20of%20the%20narrator%2C%20Kallu%20Maharaj%2C%20and%20his%20place%20in%20it.%20It%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20Bilal%20and%20his%20gang%20%E2%80%93%20young%20men%20who%20owned%20the%20alleys%20of%20Chote%20Qazipur%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20when%20I%20tell%20you%20that%20Bilal%20and%20his%20gang%20walked%20the%20alleys%20late%20at%20night%2C%20that%20they%20were%20known%20rowdies%20of%20the%20area%2C%20got%20into%20scrapes%20and%20fights%2C%20you%20have%20to%20understand%20the%20limits%20of%20their%20misdemeanours%E2%80%A6%20They%20didn%E2%80%99t%20commit%20any%20crimes%20against%20the%20state%3B%20only%20against%20good%20taste.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20outside%20world%20imposes%20itself%20on%20these%20%3Cem%3Egalis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20gang%20cannot%20remain%20unchanged%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CNothing%20hurt%20Bilal%20more%20than%20this.%20Riots%20and%20deaths%2C%20arson%20and%20murder%2C%20even%20the%20creeping%20change%20of%20names%20and%20attitudes%20were%20somethings%20we%20had%20no%20control%20over%2C%20so%20we%20tried%20not%20to%20think%20about%20them.%20But%20friendship%20was%20something%20else.%20And%20Amit%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20even%20said%20goodbye.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20against%20this%20world%20that%20is%20falling%20apart%2C%20already%20flagged%20off%20in%20the%20first%20story%2C%20that%20we%20must%20read%20the%20ones%20that%20follow%2C%20as%20they%20wander%20into%20Gorakhpur%E2%80%99s%20past%2C%20both%20real%20and%20unreal.%20Omair%20has%20that%20insider-outsider%20relationship%20to%20Gorakhpur%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthird-culture%E2%80%9D%20gaze%20which%20allows%20him%20intimacy%2C%20even%20compassion%20as%20the%20absurd%20flairs%20or%20idiocies%20of%20his%20characters%20are%20being%20etched%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-extract-a-dogs-tale-of-gossip-myth-and-mischief%5C%22%3EBook%20Extract%3A%20A%20Dog%E2%80%99s%20Tale%20of%20Gossip%2C%20Myth%20and%20Mischief%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%E2%80%98Buddha%E2%80%99s%20Smile%E2%80%99%2C%20Kallu%20Maharaj%20tells%20us%20the%20story%20of%20Knownto%20Sharma%2C%20a%20pickpocket%20whose%20command%20on%20Gorakhpur%E2%80%99s%20railway%20station%20is%20unrivalled%20until%20he%20is%20outmatched%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3Efirangi%3C%2Fem%3E%20Carnegie%20King.%20One%20of%20the%20tallest%20tales%20in%20the%20collection%20leads%20you%20to%20Deng%20Xiaoping%E2%80%99s%20origins%20in%20Gorakhpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20protagonists%2C%20equally%20larger%20than%20life%2C%20who%20are%20more%20rooted%20in%20history.%20Jalali%20Sahib%2C%20the%20protagonist%20in%20the%20story%20%E2%80%98Dagger%20in%20the%20East%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20drawn%20from%20Omair%E2%80%99s%20own%20family%20history%20that%20takes%20into%20its%20ambit%20the%20story%20of%201857%2C%20when%20Gorakhpur%20%E2%80%9Cliberated%E2%80%9D%20itself%20from%20British%20rule%20for%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJalali%20Sahib%20is%20a%20jailor%2C%20sentenced%20to%20death%20for%20having%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eopened%20the%20jail%20doors%20that%20summer%20of%201857%20to%20let%20out%20each%20and%20every%20person%20held%20under%20the%20whip%20of%20the%20Angrez%20%E2%80%93%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20for%20failure%20or%20refusal%20to%20pay%20taxes%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fomair.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22210%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-204303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22210%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOmair%20Ahmad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20as%20much%20a%20story%20of%20a%20jailor%20cheating%20death%20as%20it%20is%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Erebellious%20heart%20of%20the%20Purab%20(East)%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20touching%20upon%20the%20revolt%20of%20the%20Buddha%2C%20of%20the%20indigo%20plantations%20and%20Gandhi.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20pedantic%20lesson%20in%20history%2C%20more%20a%20reminder%20of%20how%20limited%20our%20learning%20of%20it%20is%20and%20how%20great%20the%20amnesia%20of%20our%20current%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20in%20the%20first%20story%2C%20contemporary%20events%20drop%20in%20and%20out.%20Close%20to%20the%20end%2C%20there%20is%20a%C2%A0%20mention%20of%20a%20paediatric%20doctor%20in%20charge%20of%20an%20encephalitis%20ward%20at%20the%20hospital%20%E2%80%93%20unmistakably%20a%20reference%20to%20Dr%20Kafeel%20Khan%20who%20was%20hounded%20by%20the%20government%20for%20saving%20dying%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20closest%20Omair%20comes%20to%20militating%20against%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20Gorakhpur%20has%20come%20to%20feature%20in%20the%20headlines%20but%20he%20does%20not%20set%20out%20to%20explicitly%20decode%20or%20explain%20the%20city.%20Nor%20does%20he%20lapse%20into%20romanticism%20about%20small-town%20India%20%E2%80%93%20no%20nostalgic%20descriptions%20of%20mango%20trees%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekhus%3C%2Fem%3E%20screens%20and%20lazy%20summer%20afternoons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20discussion%20on%20the%20book%2C%20the%20conversation%20veered%20to%20whether%20Gorakhpur%20is%20truly%20a%20city%20or%20a%20town.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20as%20a%20sprawling%20rapidly%20developing%20place%20with%20a%20large%20population%2C%20it%20is%20a%20city%2C%20but%20when%20you%20go%20to%20Gorakhpur%20from%20Delhi%2C%20you%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20big%20city%20person%20coming%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ehumara%20chota%20shehar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Paradoxically%2C%20the%20Gorakhpuri%20will%20also%20remind%20you%20that%20theirs%20is%20no%20small%20town%20and%20list%20all%20that%20makes%20it%20a%20bustling%20city.%20As%20Omair%20writes%20in%20the%20Author%E2%80%99s%20Note%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EIt%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20the%20content%2C%20but%20also%20the%20way%20we%20speak%20in%20out%20little%20cities%20and%20towns%2C%20how%20we%20draw%20the%20panorama%20of%20the%20world%20in%20such%20a%20way%20as%20if%20we%20are%20always%20smackdab%20in%20the%20centre%20of%20it%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20duality%20that%20Omair%20draws%20out%20with%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20characters%20and%20the%20plots%20with%20all%20their%20fantastical%20turns%20have%20a%20realism%20to%20them%20that%20evokes%20similar%20cities%20and%20towns%2C%20far%20removed%20from%20Delhi%2C%20but%20possessing%20their%20own%20sense%20of%20self.%20But%20above%20all%20it%20is%20the%20story%2C%20of%20one%20place%20and%20one%20town%20or%20city%2C%20as%20you%20will%2C%20that%20cannot%20be%20swallowed%20up%20by%20contemporary%20horrors.%20It%20is%20a%20story%20of%20Omair%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Emitti%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20%E2%80%98story-teller%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20word%20being%20bandied%20about%20with%20such%20painful%20ease%2C%20it%20is%20a%20relief%20and%20a%20pleasure%20to%20come%20across%20one%20who%20truly%20fits%20the%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERadhika%20Bordia%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693531858000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31162334%2Frajan-chaudhary-rRK6dxp4LP8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Ftelling-the-stories-of-gorakhpur-that-cant-be-swallowed-up-by-contemporary-horrors%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Omair%20Ahmad's%20'Tall%20Tales%20by%20a%20Small%20Dog'%20speaks%20directly%20to%20many%20of%20us%20today%20who%20read%20largely%20in%20English%20but%20still%20inhabit%20an%20emotional%20world%20shaped%20by%20the%20mother-tongues%20of%20our%20parents%20or%20grandparents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22