%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProposed%20in%201996%2C%20the%20arsenal%20ship%20was%20one%20of%20the%20US%20Navy's%20first%20proposed%20adaptations%20to%20the%20post-Cold%20War%20threat%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20gone%20and%20the%20Russian%20Navy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaleotti-putins-wars-how-russia-rebuilt-and-destroyed-its-military-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20shell%20of%20its%20forbear's%20strength%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20was%20little%20need%20for%20a%20large%20fleet%20dedicated%20to%20battling%20a%20first-rate%20adversary%20on%20the%20high%20seas.%20Instead%2C%20most%20threats%20were%20ground-based%20and%20either%20close%20to%20shore%20or%20farther%20inland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20reduced%20the%20number%20of%20ships%20in%20its%20inventory%20and%20focused%20on%20developing%20long-range%20strike%20capability%20for%20use%20in%20joint%20operations%20with%20other%20military%20branches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20maximize%20its%20role%20in%20this%20new%20era%2C%20the%20Navy%20proposed%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fman.fas.org%2Fdod-101%2Fsys%2Fship%2Fdocs%2Frsnlship.htm%23Costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompletely%20new%20type%20of%20warship%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20A%20massive%2C%20stealthy%2C%20highly%20automated%20vessel%20%E2%80%94%20requiring%20a%20crew%20of%20no%20more%20than%2050%20%E2%80%94%20armed%20with%20hundreds%20of%20missiles%20capable%20of%20strikes%20on%20strategic%20targets%2C%20strikes%20deep%20inside%20enemy%20territory%2C%20fire%20support%2C%20and%20air%20and%20ballistic-missile%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDubbed%20the%20%26quot%3Barsenal%20ship%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20would%20have%20up%20to%20500%20Vertical%20Launch%20System%20cells%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20any%20other%20ship%20in%20the%20fleet%20%E2%80%94%20capable%20of%20launching%20Tomahawk%20land-attack%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20SM-2%20interceptor%20missiles%2C%20and%20RIM-162%20Evolved%20Sea%20Sparrow%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20Shoup%20SM-2%20missile%20vertical%20launch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef67336f301e00193e2d90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Navy%20destroyer%20USS%20Shoup%20fires%20an%20SM-2%20missile%20from%20a%20vertical%20launch%20system%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FNeil%20Mabini%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20also%20wanted%20the%20ships%20to%20carry%20naval%20variants%20of%20the%20Hawk%20surface-to-air%20missile%2C%20the%20MGM-140%20Army%20Tactical%20Missile%20System%2C%20the%20Standoff%20Land-Attack%20Missile%2C%20and%20a%20land-attack%20variant%20of%20the%20Navy's%20Standard%20Missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20increase%20their%20interoperability%2C%20the%20arsenal%20ships%20were%20to%20have%20a%20fire-control%20capability%20that%20could%20be%20operated%20remotely%20by%20AEGIS-equipped%20vessels%20nearby%2C%20by%20Air%20Force%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.af.mil%2FAbout-Us%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F104504%2Fe-3-sentry-awacs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAWACS%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.af.mil%2FAbout-Us%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F104507%2Fe-8c-joint-stars%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJSTARS%3C%2Fa%3E%20aircraft%2C%20or%20even%20by%20ground%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20described%20the%20arsenal%20ship%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bbattleship%20of%20the%2021st%20century%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bremote%20missile%20and%20fire%20support%20magazine%26quot%3B%20and%20wanted%20to%20build%20six%20that%20it%20would%20assign%20to%20three%20two-ship%20squadrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20a